Ty is a general-purpose scripting language.

Runtime model: Bytecode interpreter + JIT

Type system:

    Gradually-typed with HM-style inference. Inferred/annotated types are
    used to guide fast-path emission in JIT functions but otherwise have
    no impact at runtime. The language is fundamentally dynamic.

Notable features/characteristics:

    + Macros
    + Pattern matching
    + C FFI
    + Stackful coroutines
    + Garbage-collected
    + Multithreading
    + Limited guardrails (!!)
